sections.text: Formation; name; title.Any agricultural association formed for the purpose of developing and improving some form of agriculture in this state which files with the Secretary of State a copy of its constitution and bylaws, shall be declared a corporation under the name and title designated in such constitution.SourceLaws 1949, c. 2, ยง 1, p. 57.
